  Description:
  This script automates the process of tracing a raster image in Adobe Illustrator using a specified preset,
  expanding the tracing, and performing a series of operations on the resulting paths.


  Scope: Intended to be run in Image Tea Action Sequencer created by Desainia Studio.
  Note: This script assumes that the tracingPresetsList variable is available in the global scope,
  as it is in Illustrator's scripting environment. You can modify the PRESET_NAME variable to use a different preset.


  Procedure:
  Step 1: Select the first RasterItem/PlacedItem.
  Step 2: Use PRESET_NAME (predefined; no UI).
  Step 3: Run item.trace() and apply preset by index.
  Step 4: Expand and ungroup tracing.
  Step 5: Select the bottom-most TOP-LEVEL path in the bottom layer. (Alert and abort if only nested paths exist.)
  Step 6: Set selected path fill to configured RGB color and remove stroke.
  Step 7: Remove the selected path.
  Step 8: Select all.
  Step 9: Group.


